<subSubSection pageId="161" pageNumber="764" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="161.[783,1376,299,722]" lastBlockId="161.[169,1375,732,1195]" pageId="161" pageNumber="764">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[783,1046,575,604]" pageId="161" pageNumber="764">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 110 mm, tail 173 mm, ear 18 mm, hindfoot 23 mm; weight 36 g. The Ethiopian Thicket Rat’s fur is uniformly grayish brown above apart from slightly darker mask around eyes, with sharply demarcated creamy-white belly. Tail is very long (157% of head-body length), semi-prehensile, and tufted. Feet have four digits on forefoot and five on relatively short hindfoot, fifth digit longer and semi-opposable. Claws are short. Chromosomal complement has 2n = 32, FN = 64.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
